sentences: Austin Roberts (born George Austin Robertson Jr.; September 19, 1945) is an American singer and songwriter.
His most successful recording was 1975's "Rocky"; a transatlantic Top 40 hit single.
Roberts was born on September 19, 1945 in Newport News, Virginia.

As the lead singer of Arkade, he had two Billboard Hot 100 hits in 1970-71, including the easy listening crossover, "The Morning of Our Lives", which became the Bridal Fair theme, later a Top 15 Adult Contemporary hit, and "Sing Out the Love (In My Heart)", which reached No. 99 on the Hot 100.

The track also reached No. 22 in the UK in November 1975, which to date is Roberts' only chart appearance in the UK.
Roberts and Hart later wrote the song "Over You" for the 1983 film, Tender Mercies.
"Over You" was nominated for the 1984 Academy Award for Best Original Song, as well as the Golden Globe nomination for Best Song in a Motion Picture.
In 1988, Roberts wrote the American Gymnastics Team's theme song for the Olympics, "When You Put Your Heart in It".
In 1999, Busch Gardens commissioned Roberts to write the opening song for their Williamsburg Extravaganza.
